If you want JSON output, then there is httpbin.<p><pre><code>  curl https://httpbin.org/ip
</code></pre>
returns<p><pre><code>  {
      &quot;origin&quot; : &quot;192.168.0.1&quot;
  }
</code></pre>
It also supports getting the user agent [0] and headers [1], among other things.<p>[0] <a href="https://httpbin.org/user-agent" rel="nofollow">https://httpbin.org/user-agent</a>
[1] <a href="https://httpbin.org/headers" rel="nofollow">https://httpbin.org/headers</a>
